"Welcome to this urge surfing practice. You are here now, and that is enough for this moment.","Find a place where you feel supported by your body and your surroundings. Maybe a chair, the floor, or a soft surface.","Think of the urge as a wave. It has a beginning, a peak, and an end. It is not permanent.","Notice where the urge lives in your body right now. Is it tight, buzzing, heavy, or moving? Just name what you notice.","Letting the urge be present without needing to act on it is a skill we are practicing.","We will just watch it move through. There is no need to push it away or follow it. Just notice it."
}

