"We are moving into the breath part of this session. Your urge is quite strong right now, and that is okay. We are not trying to push it away. We are just noticing it with a steady rhythm.","Let's try a gentle pattern together. Breathe in slowly through your nose for a count of four. Hold that breath softly for a count of four. Then breathe out slowly through your mouth like you are sighing, for a count of six.","If holding the breath feels like too much effort, just keep the exhale longer than the inhale. That is a valid way to give your body a little more space.","Inhale: one, two, three, four. Hold: one, two, three, four. Exhale: one, two, three, four, five, six.","Notice where the breath feels most active in your body right now. Maybe it is in your chest, your belly, or your shoulders. Just name it quietly to yourself.","Keep returning to that rhythm as many times as you can. Each time you breathe out, you are giving yourself a small, steady moment of noticing."
}

